<H4>    Missing Russian Diplomat Still Alive </H4>

<F P=102> BK0304095094 Bangkok THE SUNDAY POST in English 3 Apr 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> BK0304095094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok THE SUNDAY POST </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Police believe the missing Russian diplomat, third 
secretary Igor Makeev, is still alive but his whereabouts is a 
mystery. 
  A high-level police officer, who requested anonymity, said 
yesterday after he was told of Mr. Makeev's disappearance that 
several police units had launched a search for him. 
  He was last seen leaving Ocean Apartment in Soi Saladaeng 
off 
Silom Road on March 22. 
  The Institute of Forensic Medicine confirmed that Mr. Makeev 
was not on the list of dead sent to the Police Hospital. 
  Since Mr. Makeev was also responsible for looking after 
Russian women in Thailand, the police went to bars and 
nightclubs in Soi Sawatdi off Sukhumwit Road but found no traces 
of the Russian. 
  The police are awaiting confirmation from the Immigration 
Police Bureau as to whether or not Mr. Makeev has left Thailand. 

</TEXT>

