  [Text] Pyongyang, April 3 (KCNA) -- Yi Ki-taek, president 
of the South Korean opposition Democratic Party, in a statement 
April 1 denounced a reckless war blast of U.S. Secretary of 
Defense William Perry, according to a radio report from Seoul. 
  Crying about fictitious "development of nuclear weapons" by 
North Korea, the U.S. secretary of Defense said they were ready 
for a war to check it. 
  Yi condemned this as a blast designed to heighten the crisis 
on the Korean peninsula. 

