<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anti-U.S. Demonstrations in London Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anti-U.S. Demonstrations in London Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0104104694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1018 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0104104694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 1 (KCNA) -- An anti-U.S. 
demonstration was staged in London on March 26 to condemn the 
United States for aggravating the situation of the Korean 
peninsula. 
  Taking part in the demonstration were representatives of 
some 
20 political parties and organizations including the New 
Communist Party of Great Britain, the Britannic Communist Party, 
the Revolutionary Communist Party of Great Britain 
(Marxist-Leninist), the Revolutionary Communist Group of Great 
Britain, the British Anti-Imperialist Youth Organization and the 
British Organization of Solidarity with the Third World. 
  They staged a protest in front of the U.S. Embassy for 
hours, 
strongly urging Washington to stop at once threat to the DPRK 
and the "Team Spirit" and all other actions of military 
provocation. 
  The protesters contended that the nuclear issue of the 
Korean 
peninsula must be settled through DPRK-U.S. talks. 
  Speeches were made by some representatives during the 
demonstration. 
  Hugh Stephens, representative of the Britain-Korea 
Friendship 
Committee, in his speech called for the formation of a 
nonpermanent organization to defend the DPRK, noting that the 
prevailing situation was demanding a more organized movement to 
defend socialist Korea from the imperialists' moves to provoke 
another war. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

