<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Joint ROK-U.S. War Exercises Denounced </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Action on 31 Mar Reported </H4>

<F P=102> SK0204041994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0409 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0204041994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["U.S. Imperialists and South Korean Puppets Stage Surprise </F>
Strike Exercise and Gunfiring Against North" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 2 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists 
and the South Korean puppets on March 31 hurled fighter planes 
of various types including F-15s and FA-18s into the skies above 
Nyongwol, Wonju and Chunchon and staged an exercise of surprise 
strike at targets in the midst of electronic jamming, according 
to military sources. 
  In separate action that day, large-calibre artillery groups 
and heavily-armed bandits of the puppet army took firing 
positions in Cholwon County, South Korean Kangwon Province, 
Phaju and Ryonchon Counties, Kyonggi Province, and kicked up a 
war frenzy, firing over 60 105mm shells and 1,000 large-calibre 
machinegun bullets into spots near the Demilitarized Zone along 
the Military Demarcation Line. 
  On the same day, the puppets deployed scores of 
large-calibre 
guns in Cholwon County, South Korean Kangwon Province, and 
brought some 500 armed bandits into areas near Rinje and 
Ryonchon Counties. 
  Some ten helicopter gunships and transport helicopters of 
the 
puppet army flew into the skies above Ryonchon and Phochon and 
Cholwon, areas under the very nose of the North side's portion 
for a frantic exercise of support to ground attack and war 
materiel airlifting. 

</TEXT>

