<H4>    Act Called `Playing With Fire' </H4>

<F P=102> SK0304103694 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1500 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0304103694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1500 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to a military source, the U.S. 
imperialists and the South Korean puppets on 1 April perpetrated 
another round of provocative joint air war exercises against the 
North. 
  That day, formations of overseas-based pursuit-assault 
planes 
and VTOL [vertical take off and landing] assault planes of the 
U.S. Marines frenziedly staged surprise attack exercises on 
strategic objects in the Northern half of the Republic in 
coordination with airplanes of the U.S. Air Force in South Korea 
and the puppet Air Force, thus instigating an atmosphere of war. 
  This frenzied playing with fire, staged for a long in the 
skies above Yongwol, Pyongchang, Oeyon islet and Chongju, was 
designed to examine coordination striking capabilities of 
various types of military aircraft of the U.S. Marines and 
airplanes of the U.S. Air Force and the puppet Air Force against 
the North. 
  Meanwhile, tank groups of the puppet Army, which were 
mobilized and deployed in Kumpari, Paju County, fired scores of 
tank guns at areas in Hapo-ri on the other side of Imjin River, 
and armed hooligans of the puppet Army who occupied combat 
positions in Pangmong-ri fired hundreds of large-caliber machine 
gun bullets while advancing toward the Military Demarcation Line. 
  This shows that the U.S. imperialists and the South Korean 
puppets are recklessly rushing ahead toward a war against the 
North. 

</TEXT>

