burned the painting and models of Patriot missiles with the U.S. 
flags drawn on the sides. 
  About 200 police were on alert to prevent the students from 
marching into the streets. But they did not yield to it. 
  Upset by the anti-U.S demonstration of the students, the Kim 
Yong-sam pro-American flunkeyist traitorous clique posted more 
than 400 riot police in front of the U.S. Embassy, making 
itself open to criticism. 

