<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cambodia's Sihanouk Arrives in Pyongyang 4 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cambodia's Sihanouk Arrives in Pyongyang 4 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0404061794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0557 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0404061794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 4 (KCNA) -- His Majesty King 
Norodom Sihanouk of Cambodia arrived here today by special plane 
for an official goodwill visit to Korea at the invitation of 
President Kim Il-song of the Democratic People's Republic of 
Korea. 
  Their majesties the king and queen are accompanied by the 
Deputy Prime Minister in charge of the Royal Palace and Minister 
of Agriculture Kong Sam-Ol, Cambodian Ambassador E.P. 
[extraordinary and plenipotentiary] to Korea Oum Mannorine, the 
minister of state, Secretary General of the King's Cabinet 
Chhorn Hay and others. 
  The guests were met at the airport by Vice-president Yi 
Chong-ok, Vice-premier and Foreign Minister Kim Yong-nam and 
officials concerned. 
  They were met at the airport by Chinese Ambassador to Korea 
Qiao Zonghuai. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-4612 </DOCNO>
