<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-064 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  2 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conference of Party Cell Secretaries Concludes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conference of Party Cell Secretaries Concludes </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meeting Recapped </H4>

<F P=102> SK0204105894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1033 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0204105894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 2 (KCNA) -- The national conference 
of party cell secretaries which opened here Thursday [31 March] 
ended today, winding up its work successfully. 
  The conference initiated by the dear leader Comrade Kim 
Chong-il was the first historic meeting of its kind ever since 
the foundation of the Workers' Party of Korea (October 10, 1945). 
  The great leader President Kim Il-song sent a letter of 
congratulations to the delegates to the conference to warmly 
congratulate the delegates and all party cell secretaries 
throughout the country and clearly indicate the highly important 
tasks and ways of effecting a new turn in party cell work as 
required by the development of the party and the revolution. 
  Many delegates took the floor at the conference, including 
Kim Yu-pong, a party cell secretary of the February 8 Chiktong 
youth coal mine; Ko Tae-chon, a party cell secretary of the 
Hwanghae iron and steel complex; Kim Si-pong, a party cell 
secretary of the Pyongyang locomotive corps; Won Chol-hui, a 
party cell secretary of the Sariwon textile mill; Yi Yang-nam, a 
party cell secretary of the Haeju cement factory; Yu Sok-kun, a 
party cell secretary of Kim Il- song University; and Pak Won-u, 
a party cell secretary of the Taedoksan cooperative farm in 
Changpung County. 
  The speakers said the conference was a meeting of loyalty 
which demonstrated the rock-firm faith and will of the cell 
secretaries and members of the whole party to share the destiny 
with the party forever and accomplish the socialist cause of 
chuche, and a historic occasion of great importance in building 
up the party ranks into a steel-like unit and strengthening the 
driving force of the Korean revolution in every way. 
  They praised dear Comrade Kim Chong-il as the outstanding 
leader of a revolutionary party of the working class in the 
present time who comprehensively expounded the unique idea and 
theories of party building and successfully solved all 
theoretical and practical matters in enhancing the function and 
role of party cells. 
  They renewed their determination to creditably discharge 
their honorable mission and duty as party cell secretaries in 
constantly strengthening the WPK into an impregnable party and 
increasing its militancy and leadership ability in every way 
under the leadership of the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il in 
hearty response to the great leader Comrade Kim Il-song's letter 
of congratulations to the delegates to the conference. 
  A letter of pledge to President Kim Il-song and Comrade Kim 
Chong-il was adopted at the conference. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-4613 </DOCNO>
