<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conference of Party Cell Secretaries Concludes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conference of Party Cell Secretaries Concludes </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Delegates on Kim Il-song Letter </H4>

<F P=102> SK0204105694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1026 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0204105694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 2 (KCNA) -- The letter of 
congratulations of the great leader Comrade Kim Il-song to the 
delegates to the national conference of party cell secretaries 
now in session here has evoked great repercussions on party 
officials and working people. 
  Yi Yong-kil, secretary of the Yanggang Provincial Committee 
of the Workers' Party of Korea, said: 
  "The great leader's letter of congratulations is an immortal 
banner to enhance the function and role of party cells, the 
basic organisations, strengthen our party into an unconquerable 
party and increase its leadership ability, and a powerful weapon 
to bring into full play the advantages and vitality of socialism 
in our country. 
  "The provincial party committee will effectively conduct the 
organisational and political work to thoroughly fulfil the 
militant tasks set out in the letter of congratulations so that 
all party cell secretaries and party members in the province may 
live and work as the vanguard fighters of the revolution should." 
  Yi Sung-nam, chief secretary of the Kangdong County, 
Pyongyang municipality, party committee, said: 
  "The great leader's letter of congratulations is a highly 
important guideline for our people's struggle to strengthen the 
party and promote the general march of socialism of our own 
style. I will make my utmost efforts to build up all the party 
cells in the county to be cornerstones and powerful militant 
units loyal to the guidance of the dear leader Comrade Kim 
Chong-il." 
  No Tu-chol, vice-chairman of the state planning commission, 
said: 
  "The great leader in his letter of congratulations laid 
stress again on the need to uphold the unified leadership of the 
party Central Committee with loyalty, thus providing a powerful 
weapon to immensely strengthen the ideological and moral unity 
and cohesion of our revolutionary ranks around the dear leader. 
  "We will take it as the key point in our work to establish 
the unified leadership system of the party, full of pride in 
having the illustrious leader and confidence in victory of the 
revolution and, at the same time, creditably attain the main 
objectives of the party's revolutionary economic strategy, thus 
positively contributing to defending and exalting our socialism 
centred on the masses." 
  Chang Chun-sik, a party cell secretary of the Tokchon coal 
mine, said: 
  "We will conduct the party activities better with loyalty to 
the party and the leader, confidence in victory in the socialist 
cause and indomitable will, no matter how the situation may 
change, so as to build up our party cell into a cornerstone 
firmly supporting the party and socialism." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-4615 </DOCNO>
