<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conference of Party Cell Secretaries Concludes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conference of Party Cell Secretaries Concludes </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Radio Reports Proceedings </H4>

<F P=102> SK0204121694 </F>
<F P=103> SK0204121694 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on proceedings at the Workers' Party of Korea cell 
secretaries meeting held from 31 March to 2 April at the 
Pyongyang Gymnasium in Pyongyang. 
  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean at 
0500 GMT on 31 March carries a 168-minute recorded report on the 
first day morning session of national party cell secretaries 
meeting. The announcer says O Chin-u, Kang Song-san, Yi 
Chong-ok, Pak Song-chol, Kim Yong-chu, Kim Yong-nam, Choe Kwang, 
Kye Ung-tae, Han Song-yong, So Yun-sok, Kim Chol-man, Choe 
Tae-pok, and others are on hand. 
  Kim Ki-nam delivers a opening speech, noting the 
significance 
of the first opening of a party cells meeting. 
  Kye Ung-tae reads a congratulatory letter from Kim Il-song 
to 
the delegates of the meeting. 
  Kim Ki-nam delivers a report, noting the meeting is convened 
by Kim Chong-il and the significance of party cells. 
  The first session ends after children's union members read a 
congratulatory message in which Kim Chong-il is admired as a 
warmhearted parent of party cell secretaries. 
  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean at 
1000 GMT on 31 March carries a 90-minute recorded report on 
first day afternoon session of national party cell secretaries 
meeting. 
  Party cell secretaries speak about achievements made by each 
party cell in indoctrinating party members and masses in 
fulfilling tasks assigned to each unit and attribute those 
successful achievements mainly to Kim Chong-il's wise 
leadership, and stresses the importance of people holding the 
spirit of self-reliance and fortitude. They express their will 
to protect party, leader and to raise party members as 
revolutionaries loyal to party. 
  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean at 
0500 GMT on 1 April carries a 78-minute recorded report on 
second day morning session of national meeting of party cell 
secretaries. 
  Party cell secretaries recall Kim Chong-il's love for people 
and report on their achievements. One party secretary resolves 
to strengthen party cells' role in implementing party's policy. 
  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean at 
1000 GMT on 1 April carries a 75-minute recorded report on 
second day afternoon session of party cell secretaries meeting. 
  Party secretaries continue to discuss Kim Chong-il guidance 
for effectively carrying out revolutionary tasks and 
encouragement and benevolence extended to cell secretaries. 
  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean at 
0500 GMT on 2 April carries a 65-minute recorded report of the 
final session of national meeting of party cell secretaries. 
  Party cell secretaries continue discussions and adopt a 
letter of resolution to Kim Il-song and Kim Chong-il. Details 
of the letter are not given. 
  Kye Ung-tae delivers a closing speech in which he describes 
the success of the meeting. He says this was a meeting in which 
party cell secretaries' will to devote themselves to the 
fatherland was displayed and urges cell secretaries to 
thoroughly implement party's military policies. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-4616 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas064_c_94025" </HT>


