<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conference of Party Cell Secretaries Concludes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conference of Party Cell Secretaries Concludes </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Delegates Awarded at Ceremony </H4>

<F P=102> SK0304085294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0814 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0304085294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 3 (KCNA) -- A ceremony for awarding 
state decorations and gifts to delegates to the national 
conference of party cell secretaries was held here Saturday. 
  Present at the ceremony were Kye Ung-tae, member of the 
Political Bureau and secretary of the Central Committee of the 
Workers' Party of Korea [WPK], Kim Chung-nin and Kim Kuk-tae, 
secretaries of the WPK Central Committee, leading officials of 
the WPK Central Committee and the delegates to the conference. 
  Citations of the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il were 
awarded to 121 delegates to the conference who have set examples 
in implementing the party policy and carrying out their 
revolutionary tasks by pushing ahead with the three revolutions, 
ideological, technical and cultural, in hearty response to the 
programme of modelling the whole society on the chuche idea. 
  The Order of National Flag first class was conferred on 56 
delegates, the Labour Order on 852 delegates, the Order of 
National Flag second class on 2,957 delegates and the Order of 
National Flag third class on 4,305 delegates. 
  Gifts of the WPK Central Committee were awarded to the 
entire 
delegates. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

