<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conference of Party Cell Secretaries Concludes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conference of Party Cell Secretaries Concludes </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Yi In-mo Meets With Secretaries </H4>

<F P=102> SK0404082894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0555 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0404082894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 4 (KCNA) -- Many delegates to the 
national conference of party cell secretaries including those 
who were awarded the title of labour hero of the DPRK and 
honored with letters of commendation from the dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il, met here Sunday with Yi In-mo, a former 
war correspondent of the Korean People's Army and veteran party 
member who is widely known as the incarnation of faith and will. 
  Upon meeting them, Yi In-mo recalled the days right after 
the 
liberation of the country when he was making strenuous efforts 
to rouse people of broad strata to the struggle for democratic 
reforms including the agrarian reform, upholding the line of 
nation building set forth by the great leader President Kim 
Il-song. 
  He said he told his comrades who were with him in South 
Korea 
and visitors that his birthday is October 10, the founding 
anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. "I did so," he went 
on, "not because I forgot my birthday, but because I wanted to 
celebrate the party founding anniversary together with the 
people of the homeland, remembering at any time and in any place 
that I am a member of the Workers' Party of Korea, and always 
thinking of the party." 
  He said each time the enemy tried to force him to write a 
"paper of ideological conversion" he tore it to pieces and threw 
them at their faces, his mind crowded with thought of our 
general and consciousness of being a party member. 
  Noting that the great leader and the dear leader are the 
greatest in the world, he asked the party cell secretaries to do 
a lot of more work, remaining loyal subjects who uphold Comrade 
Kim Chong-il with unquestioned worship. 
  The visitors vowed to hold President Kim Il-song and Comrade 
Kim Chong-il in high esteem and follow them, build their party 
cells well and constantly strengthen and develop them, as Yi 
In-mo asked them to. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-4620 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas064_c_94029" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-064 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  4 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conference of Party Cell Secretaries Concludes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conference of Party Cell Secretaries Concludes </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kim Il-song Meets With Delegates </H4>

<F P=102> SK0404103594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1026 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0404103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 4 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song on April 4 met and congratulated the 
delegates to the national conference of party cell secretaries. 
  When President Kim Il-song arrived, the delegates 
enthusiastically welcomed him with stormy cheers of "hurrah!". 
  He was presented with a basket of fragrant flowers 
representing boundless reverence and loyal heart of the party 
cell secretaries of the whole party. 
  Present there were member of the Presidium of the Political 
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party [WPK] of 
Korea O Chin-u, members of the Political Bureau of the C.C. 
[Central Committee], the WPK Yi Chong-ok, Pak Song-chol and Kim 
Yong-chu and other members and alternate members of the 
Political Bureau and secretaries of the C.C., the WPK. 
  President Kim Il-song congratulated the delegates who had 
made great contributions to strengthening and developing the 
party into an invincible revolutionary party and further 
consolidating our socialist stronghold by raising the militant 
function and role of the party cells and posed for a photograph 
with them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
