<H4>    Vo Van Kiet Leaves for Cambodia </H4>

<F P=102> BK0204084494 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
2300 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0204084494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At the invitation of Samdech Krompreah Norodom 
Ranariddh and Samdech Hun Sen, first and second prime ministers 
of the government of Kingdom of Cambodia, our Prime Minister Vo 
Van Kiet left Hanoi this morning 2 April for an official visit 
to the Kingdom of Cambodia. 
  Escorting Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet were the Foreign 
Affairs 
Minister Nguyen Manh Cam; Trade Minister Le Van Triet; Tran Hong 
Quan, minister of education and training; Customs General 
Director Truong Quang Duoc; Nguyen Ngoc Tran, chairman of the 
central Overseas Vietnamese Commission; Le Minh Nghia, chairman 
of the government Border Commission; Nguyen Quoc Mau, deputy 
head of Government Office; Vu Quoc Tuan, assistant to the prime 
minister; and Tran Huy Chuong, Vietnamese ambassador to the 
Kingdom of Cambodia. 

</TEXT>

