<H4>    NHAN DAN Hails Vo Van Kiet Visit </H4>

<F P=102> BK0204094194 Hanoi VNA in English 0643 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0204094194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA April 2 -- Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet's 
arrival in Phnom Penh expected this morning for an official 
visit to Cambodia affirmed the determination of the two 
countries' leadership to improve the close neighbours' 
relations, consolidate their traditional friendship and promote 
their cooperation and mutual asistance, says the national paper 
NHAN DAN in an editorial today. 
  The editorial further says: `The visits to Vietnam of the 
two 
Cambodian prime ministers, Mr Krom Preah Norodom Ranarridh and 
Mr Hun Sen, and of Cambodia's National Assembly chairman and 
acting head of state, Mr Chea Sim, earlier this year ushered in 
a new period of the two countries' relations'. 
  `The visit of Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet indicates the 
consistent policy of the Vietnamese Government to solve the 
problems left behind by the history and accelerate the all-sided 
cooperation between the two countries in the new situation', 
notes the editorial. 
  It also expersses the belief that his visit will bring in 
fine results contributing to the promotion, consolidation and 
development of the neighbourliness, the traditional friendship 
and cooperation between the two countries. 

</TEXT>

