<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Summit Talks Held With Cambodian Leaders </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Summit Talks Held With Cambodian Leaders </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Ranariddh Gives Banquet Speech </H4>

<F P=102> BK0304145494 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0304145494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dear friends, in Phnom Penh on the evening of 2 
April, the Royal Government of the Kingdom of Cambodia solemnly 
hosted a banquet in honor of the visiting Vietnamese Government 
delegation led by Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet. 
  At the banquet, Samdech Norodom Ranariddh, first prime 
minister of the Royal Government of the Kingdom of Cambodia 
delivered a speech. He said: 
  [Begin Ranariddh recording, in Cambodian fading into 
Vietnamese translation] His Excellency the Prime Ministers, 
Their Highnesses, Distinguished ladies and gentlemen: 
  On behalf of Samdech Norodom Sihanouk, the King of Cambodia, 
the Royal Government of the Kingdom of Cambodia has the honor to 
welcome His Excellency Vo Van Kiet, prime minister of the SRV, 
and his entourage. Samdech Hun Sen and I are very pleased to 
meet again with His Excellency the Vietnamese prime minister and 
other high-ranking officials of the Vietnamese Government in our 
land. 
  His Excellency Vo Van Kiet warmly welcomed our delegation on 
a visit to Vietnam in August 1993. During the visit, we 
exchanged views on various issues of our respective countries 
and those of the region. It was a great honor for our 
delegation to be received by His Excellency Le Duc Anh, 
president of the SRV, and His Excellency Do Muoi, general 
secretary of the Communist Party of Vietnam. Through that visit, 
we have gained new ideas about the Cambodia- Vietnam cooperation 
relations, especially our determination to continue talks on 
various issues which are aimed at expanding cooperation between 
our two nations. 
  We unanimously agreed that we will give priority to 
cooperation projects related to the economic, trade, 
scientific-technological, tourism, and other essential domains. 
We still have many issues that require consistent consultation 
and discussion so as to strengthen and develop the relations of 
friendship and cooperation between our two peoples. 
  We have but a common mission; I am convinced that our two 
states and governments have the same aspiration of maintaining 
long and lasting peace, security, and stability. 
  We have built a fine, healthy atmosphere with an aim to 
consolidate the relations of friendship, cooperation, and good 
neighborliness. These are factors that help strengthen 
relations between our two peoples. Our struggle for prosperity 
and happiness at present not only serves the interest of peace 
and stability in the Southeast Asia region, but also in the 
Asia-Pacific and the world. 
  On this occasion, I would like to express the Royal 
Government of the Kingdom of Cambodia's gratitude to the SRV 
Government for its positive contribution to restoring peace and 
stability in Cambodia through the signing of the 23 October 1991 
Paris Agreement on Cambodia. We still have many important 
issues to be resolved. We are confident, however, that we can 
resolve them through the principle of respecting each other's 
national independence, sovereignty, territorial integrity, and 
noninterference to each other's internal affairs as well as in 
the spirit of respecting the Kingdom of Cambodia's neutrality. 
  His Excellency the Prime Minister, on behalf of the Royal 
Government of the Kingdom of Cambodia, I would like to express 
our appreciation on U.S. President Bill Clinton's correct 
decision to lift the U.S. trade embargo against Vietnam. This 
has created new relations between the United States and the SRV 
and through which various nations in the region are gaining 
potential to quickly develop their economies. 
  Excellencies, ladies and gentlemen, I would like to ask you, 
together with me, to turn our attention to a great personage who 
has brought about peace to the Kingdom of Cambodia: Samdech 
Norodom Sihanouk. 
  I have the honor to invite His Excellency the Prime 
Minister, 
Their Highnesses, ladies and gentlemen to a toast for the good 
health of Samdech Norodom Sihanouk, the esteemed King of the 
Cambodian people. 
  I would like also to propose a toast for the good health and 
happiness of His Excellency Le Duc Anh, president of the SRV, 
and of His Excellency Vo Van Kiet, prime minister of the SRV; 
for the happiness and prosperity of the Vietnamese and Cambodia 
peoples; for the good health and success of Their Highnesses; 
and for the good health of Excellencies, Samdech Hun Sen, and 
all ladies and gentlemen who are present here. 
  Thank you very much. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

