<H3> <TI>   Czech Delegation Departs Hanoi for South </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Czech Delegation Departs Hanoi for South </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0104154394 Hanoi VNA in English 1430 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0104154394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Apr 1 -- A delegation of the Czech 
parliament led by Mr Milan Uhde, speaker of the lower house, 
left Hanoi for the south this morning, continuing its official 
visit to Vietnam. The delegation was accompanied by deputy head 
of the National Assembly's External Relations Commission Tran 
Van Phac. During its stay in Hanoi, the Czech delegation met 
with Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam and called at Dong Nam A 
Brewery. Meanwhile Mrs Milan Uhde visited some cultural, social 
establishments and place of historic interest. 

</TEXT>

