<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Students Demonstrate Against Rice Imports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Students Demonstrate Against Rice Imports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0304095794 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0905 GMT 3 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0304095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Pusan Broadcasting Bureau] </F>
  [Text] About 2,000 college students affiliated with the 
Korean Federation of University Student Councils [Hanchongnyon] 
have been holding a rally of second-term deputies of 
Hanchongnyon at Pusan University since 2 April. They gathered 
at the Pusan Railway Station this afternoon and held a rally 
opposing the opening of the rice market. They are presently 
staging a street demonstration along the sidewalks in Pusan and 
are moving toward Kwangbok-tong, their second assembly site. 
  In a news conference held previously, Hanchongnyon revealed 
that it will hold a general rally at Konkuk University in Seoul 
on 5 April to oppose the government's Uruguay Round 
negotiations, and that all universities and colleges throughout 
the country decided to go on a strike for two days on 8 and 9 
April. 
  In addition, Hanchongnyon will hold a pan-citizens rally to 
oppose rice imports and the opening of its market in Seoul on 16 
April, and about 200 of its executive members decided to go on 
an indefinite hunger strike in front of the National Assembly 
Hall. 
  Hanchongnyon resolved to hold a ceremony marking the 
inauguration of the second-term of Hanchongnyon in Choson 
University in Kwangju for four days beginning 27 May. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

