<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Yong-sam Replaces Agriculture Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Yong-sam Replaces Agriculture Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0404070294 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0633 GMT 4 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0404070294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Kim Chin-sok from Chongwadae, presidential </F>
office -- live] 
  [Text] Today, President Kim Yong-sam replaced Kim Yang-pae, 
minister of agriculture, forestry, and fisheries; with Choe 
In-ki, former vice minister of home affairs; in connection with 
Minister Kim's responsibility for the controversial revision of 
the Uruguay Round implementation plan. 
  When announcing the reshuffle of the minister of 
agriculture, 
forestry, and fisheries today, Chu Ton-sik, spokesman for 
Chongwadae [presidential office], said: President Kim Yong-sam 
admitted that the Uruguay Round implementation plan had been 
revised for farmers and would be beneficial to them. However, 
Minister Kim had told the people, as well as the president, that 
he would not correct even one word of the implementation plan. 
Therefore, by revising this plan, he deceived the people and 
the president and tarnished the morality of the civilian regime. 
So, the president had no alternative but to hold the minister 
responsible and replaced the minister with the former vice 
minister of home affairs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

