<H3> <TI>   Swedish Prime Minister Bildt Arrives for Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Swedish Prime Minister Bildt Arrives for Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0304150094 Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network in Malay 
1300 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0304150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Malay </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Swedish Prime Minister Carl Bildt arrived in Kuala 
Lumpur today for a three-day official visit to Malaysia. This 
first visit to Malaysia by a Swedish head of government was 
welcomed by Foreign Minister Datuk Abdullah Ahmad Badawi at the 
Kuala Lumpur International Airport. 
  The Swedish prime minister, who is scheduled to hold talks 
with Datuk Sri Dr. Mahathir and Deputy Prime Minister Datuk Sri 
Anwar Ibrahim, is visiting Malaysia at the invitation of the 
government. He is also scheduled to attend a briefing at the 
Economic Planning Unit of the Prime Minister's Department, meet 
with Malaysian businessmen based in Sweden [as heard], and visit 
the Proton car plant in Shah Alam. 
  Malaysia has signed several bilateral agreements with 
Sweden, 
namely a technical and economic cooperation agreement, a double 
taxation avoidance agreement, an investment guarantee agreement, 
and an air services agreement. 

