  [Text] His Excellency [H.E.] Vo Van Kiet, prime minister 
of the SRV, and his colleagues arrived in Phnom Penh, capital of 
the Kingdom of Cambodia, at 0910 this morning for an official 
two-day visit from 2 to 3 April 1994, at the invitation of the 
heads of the Royal Government of Cambodia [RGC] Prince Krompreah 
Norodom Ranariddh and Samdech Hun Sen. 
  Upon its arrival at Pochentong international airport, the 
high-ranking SRV delegation was highly and cordially welcomed by 
Prince Krompreah Norodom Ranariddh, first prime minister, and 
Samdech Hun Sen, second prime minister of the RGC. Prince 
Kromkhun Norodom Sirivut, deputy prime minister and minister of 
foreign affairs and international cooperation; H.E. Sar Kheng, 
deputy prime minister and co-minister of interior and security; 
and many officials, and youth scouts were also there. Diplomats 
from various countries accredited to the Kingdom of Cambodia 
were also present. 
  It is expected that during this visit H.E. Vo Van Kiet will 
meet with Samdech Chea Sim, acting head of state and chairman of 
the National Assembly, and hold bilateral talks with Prince 
Krompreah Norodom Ranariddh and Samdech Hun Sen. 

