<H3> <TI>   Coalition Members Form Defense Policy Group </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Coalition Members Form Defense Policy Group </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0504083194 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 5 Apr 94 
Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0504083194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Interested Diet members of the ruling coalition 
parties will start a new policy study group, "Study Group on 
Japan's Security and Future Course [Nihon no Anzen Hosho to 
Shinro wo Kangaeru Kai]," on 6 April. Yukihisa Yoshida, 
Democratic Socialist Party member of the upper house, will be 
the chairman of the group, and members will include Tatsuro 
Matsumae, member of the Socialist Democratic Party of Japan 
upper house; Hideaki Tamura, member of Shinseito [Japan Renewal 
Party] upper house; and Natsuo Yamaguchi, memebr of Komeito 
lower house. Moves, mostly initiated by Shinseito, to form study 
groups across party boundaries on specific policy issues have 
been quite active after a plan to form a "Policy Study Group" of 
all ruling coalition parties to discuss overall policy failed to 
take off. However, this will be the first time a policy group 
on defense will be formed. 

</TEXT>

