<H3> <TI>   MONTSAME Publishes Press Reviews </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MONTSAME Publishes Press Reviews </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Press Review for 2 Apr </H4>

<F P=102> OW0204155794 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1313 GMT 2 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0204155794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 2 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
newspaper, ARDIYN ERH informs that discussion of the draft law 
on state service at the State Great Hural (SGH) spring session 
is being continued. 
  The newspaper informs that at the government regular sitting 
a particular attention has been paid to the issues of food 
supply of the population. A report on this issue has been made 
by the Minister of Food and Agriculture of Mongolia T. Oold. 
The government has pointed out to necessity of consolidation of 
some progress in food supply of the population. As the 
newspaper informs, the government has instructed the minister of 
external relations to make certain amendments in the agreement 
on the regime of border communication between Mongolia and 
China. The newspaper informs that the government has decided to 
submit for consideration to the State Great Hural an issue about 
Mongolia's joining the New York convention concerning activity 
of arbitration organizations. 
  The newspaper comments the speech made by the Deputy 
Chairman 
of the Federal Assembly of the Russian Federation R. Abdulatipov 
in connection with the statement of this political figure about 
territorial claims of Mongolia to Russia. 
  The Vice Minister of External Relations of Mongolia J. 
Choinhor has expressed bewilderment of Mongolian side and 
expressed regret at the fact that high ranking officials permit 
themselves to make such statements. The newspaper informs that 
the director of the press service of the Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs of Russia G. Karasin has noted in his statement at the 
press conference that there are no disagreements of territorial 
issues between Russia and Mongolia. 
  According to information of the officials given in the 
newspaper, in the country a big attention is being paid to 
problems of exploitation of oil deposits. As the newspaper 
notes, measures are being taken of abolition of shortcomings and 
omissions in activity of the company, which is responsible for 
exploitation of old deposits. 
  The Mongolian Army newspaper, TUSGAAR TOGTNOL, publishes a 
report made by the vice minister of defence, chief of the 
General Staff of the Armed Forces of the country Major General 
R. Gabaa at the grand meeting devoted to the 73rd anniversary of 
foundation of the present Armed Forces of Mongolia. 
  In the report a great attention is paid to solution of 
social 
problems of military servicemen. 
  Vice doctor of historical science, Colonel B. Badarch writes 
in the newspaper about tasks of the Armed Forces in renewal of 
their activity, strengthening of discipline and order. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

