<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   MNDP Joins IDU at Conference in Australia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MNDP Joins IDU at Conference in Australia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0404144994 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1229 GMT 4 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0404144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 4 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
Mongolian National Democratic Party (MNDP), one of the leading 
opposition political forces of Mongolia, has joined the 
International Democratic Union [IDU] in the course of the 
regular conference held in Sydney of this international 
organization which includes more than 30 parties and 
organizations of various countries of Asia, Africa, Caribean 
region, Europe, Latin America and Asia and Pacific region as 
well. Now the MNDP became the 35th member of the organization. 
  The admission of the MNDP to the IDU is to serve as a 
significant step for further promoting the process of democracy 
and renovation of Mongolian society, notes D. Ganbold in his 
interview granted to the MONTSAME correspondent. He has just 
returned to Ulaanbaatar after his participation in the Sydney 
conference of the international organization. 

</TEXT>

