<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Human Casualties in Large Steppe Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No Human Casualties in Large Steppe Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0404145094 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1229 GMT 4 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0404145094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 4 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Dozens of 
herdsmen's gers, a national dwelling, and large pasture area 
were on fire and hundreds of head of cattle perished due to the 
steppe fire extending throughout the territory of a number of 
somons of the two eastern aymags of Mongolia, namely Suhbaatar 
and Dornod ones. Burnt in a fire lasting one and half day was 
an area 300 km long and 150 km wide. Fortunately, there are not 
any human casualties recorded in connection with this fire. 
  According to the MONTSAME correspondent from the Suhbaatar 
aymag, the fire flared up firstly on the territory of the 
Munhhaan somon of the aymag. So far the reason for the fire to 
have broken out has not been established. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

