<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senegal Signs Information Cooperation Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Senegal Signs Information Cooperation Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3003053394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0502 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3003053394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 30 (KCNA) -- An agreement on 
cooperation in information was signed in Dakar on March 24 
between the governments of the Democratic People's Republic of 
Korea and the Republic of Senegal. 
  It was signed by Abdoulay Elimane, minister of information 
of 
Senegal, and Yi Song-nin, DPRK ambassador to Senegal. 

</TEXT>

