<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 5 KYODO -- The head of the influential 
business leaders' group expressed his optimistic outlook on the 
economy Tuesday [5 April], saying it is heading for a steady 
recovery. 
  "Economic indicators are increasingly showing the evidence 
(that the economy is on the rise) and corporate sentiment is 
gradually improving," said Masaru Hayami, chairman of the Japan 
Association of Corporate Executives (Keizai Doyukai), at a 
regular news conference. But Hayami, calling the yen's advance 
against the U.S. dollar "excessive," said, "the current 
dollar-yen level will have an adverse effect on export-oriented 
companies." 
  "The U.S. Administration apparently hopes the yen will post 
a 
further gain in the face of a `triple' decline of stocks, bonds 
and dollars," Hayami said. 

