<F P=103> BK0504091194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA April 5 -- The Trans-Vietnam 500-kv 
[kilovolt] power transmission line began test operation this 
morning, announced the Ministry of Energy. 
  In anticipation of the commission of the north-south line, 
the eighth and also the last turbine generator of the Hoa Binh 
Hydro-Electric Power Plant was officially hooked to the national 
grid yesterday after seven days' test run. 
  Since the first generator unit of the Hoa Binh 
Hydro-Electric 
Power Plant was operational on Dec. 31, 1988, the plant has 
supplied 17.108 billion kwh [kilowatt hours]. 

